{
"script": "Deep inside a flooded cave, the diver reached a fork and had to choose a direction. He'd done this dive before and felt confident, so he never bothered to check his guideline. He turned left. But the way out was right, and the tunnel behind him was already swallowing his trail in thick clouds of silt. And with every kick, he swam further from the only exit. His air gauge dropped. The passages narrowed. By the time he realized his mistake, he couldn't even turn his body around. One wrong turn in the dark, and the cave kept him forever.",
